,"updated_at":"2016-03-22T17:19:26Z","closed_at":"2015-04-02T01:20:58Z","author_association":"NONE","type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"Hi all,\nlet's say I've a gulp task like the 'scripts' task below where:\n- the gulp.src glob is modified by the specified 'base' path\n- the stream is saved to disk by gulp.desc with folder prefix\n\nIn the watcher I need to handle the 'deleted' event type deleting the corresponding file into the dest folder and I'm wondering if there exists a smarter way than the one i came up with.\n\nBetter said: can anyone translate my stuff to proper gulp? :)\nThanks in advance.\n\nOh, last question: in a case like this is it ok to not provide a callback to the del task?\n\n``` javascript\ngulp.task('scripts', function() {\n    return gulp.src('src/**/*.js', {base: 'src'})\n        .pipe(indent({tabs: true, amount: 1}))\n        .pipe(header('(function () {\\r\\n\\t\\'use strict\\'\\r\\n'))\n        .pipe(footer('\\r\\n})();'))\n        .pipe(gulp.dest('build'));\n});\n\ngulp.task('watch', function () {\n    gulp.watch('src/**/*.js', ['scripts'])\n        .on('change', function (event) {\n            if (event.type === 'deleted') {\n\n                // Simulating the {base: 'src'} used with gulp.src in the scripts task\n                var filePathFromSrc = path.relative(path.resolve('src'), event.path);\n\n                //Concatenating the \"build\" absolute path used by gulp.dest in the scripts task\n                var destFilePath = path.resolve('build', filePathFromSrc); \n\n                del(destFilePath);\n            }\n        });\n});\n```\n","closed_by":{"login":"phated","id":992373,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk5MjM3Mw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/992373?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/phated","html_url":"h